article.description: Ben Millaud-Meunier made four 3-pointers and scored 18 points, Malik Harmon added 17 points, and St. Francis (Pa.) beat Lehigh 84-73 on Wednesday night for the Mountain Hawks' seventh straight lo
article.headline: St. Francis (Pa) beats Lehigh 84-73
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Ben Millaud-Meunier made four 3-pointers and scored 18 points, Malik Harmon added 17 points, and St. Francis (Pa.) beat Lehigh 84-73 on Wednesday night for the Mountain Hawks' seventh straight loss. Isaiah Blackmon scored 16 points with a career-high four steals, and Josh Nebo and Ronnie Drinnon each scored 12 for the Red Flash (3-3). Harmon and Drinnon combined to make 14 of 20 St. Francis free throws. Trailing 41-36 at halftime, Lehigh's Austin Price and Jesse Chuku each hit 3s amid an 11-4 run and the Mountain Hawks pulled within 59-54, but the Red Flash replied with a 9-2 run and led 68-56 with 7:14 to go after Blackmon's layup. Harmon made 6 of 8 St. Francis free throws in the final 1:06 and the Red Flash held on. Tim Kempton led Lehigh with 18 points on 7-of-15 shooting. Kahron Ross added 16, Price 12 and Chuku 11.
